HEADWORD: Jharal
<hw>Jha"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A wild goat (<spn>Capra Jemlaica</spn>) which
inhabits the loftiest mountains of India. It has long, coarse hair,
forming a thick mane on its head and neck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jib</ent>⟦br⟧
